The "Teaching What I Most Need to Know" Section:
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

To know full and pure love is a matter of rising to your highest 
self, being willing to accept the other fully and with an 
understanding heart.  There must be complete and full trust between 
you and the other, which also serves to clear away your and the 
other's issues, making it possible for you both to approach the world 
with clear eyes and joyful optimistic hearts.

Take care in who you trust for a romantic relationship by listening 
to your feelings, but when you find that right person who you know 
you can trust, give it your all and then some more.  You will find 
sides of your self that you hadn't even imagined, blooming freely in 
the light of love.  And remember always - a relationship is not a 
thing from which you need gain, but rather, a joining to which you 
give and thereby fully know who you are.

The risks are so worth the incredible feeling of having an 
undying bond and trust with the one you love.  Your expanding 
fullness will come from giving to and boosting up another to untold 
dimension, as the other will give to you.  Love expands and heals.  
Let not fear enter your heart in life or love.  Cast it out until 
only feelings based in love remain.  Do this by facing your feelings 
honestly, knowing them, and sharing them.

This giving and building includes letting that person grow and go
should that be what they need.  Be true to them always in all ways.  
But be true to yourself first and foremost, thereby being true to 
the other.  

Should your relationship not be able to carry forward for all the
time you live, remember that success in a relationship is not based
on its length.  Success in relationships, and all other things, is
based on the fullness of your soul.

Telling of God's Assured Love,

